    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "For manually seeing what's going on, can use \n```\ncurl -X GET \"http://localhost:5051/eth/v1/events?topics=voluntary_exit\" -H \"accept: text/event-stream\"\n```\nany event really, use 'head' if you want to see a lot of events, or something like voluntary exit above if you want to see just the comments...\n\n```\nsseClient.sendComment(\" \");\n```\nwill send a comment on the stream to a client, that's the new feature I added in javalin 4.2.0 to use for this ticket. We don't need to send anything really in a comment, could test if empty string works rather than space, otherwise just a space will suffice.\n\nhttps://github.com/ConsenSys/teku/pull/4844\n\nThere was a commit here that implemented the keepalive poorly, but I've left in the test suite functionality to count comments.",
